\id XXA OVERVIEW.INL Inland Nyangumarta This is the latest .INL version. It stems from DT 6Jun95 rev BT 19Sep95 compared carefully with SB's .NTH version of 22Oct95, and modified by us to achieve our prefs, 25Oct95. Minor adjmts PP 27Nov95 and a few from us (esp #14, 20) in Jan96, and finalised with DT 13-27Mar96
\h Overview
\toc1 Nyungurrangu Payipulja Muwarrarrangu
\toc2 Overview
\mt1 Nyungurrangu Payipulja Muwarrarrangu
\mt1 Walangkarranguja Yajarnayarninyi Yakujun
\ip Unknown if consultant checked.
\imt1 Nyungulu mirli-mirlilu kalkurnajaninyi muwarr marlu Payipulja. Miranu wantuluman palarranguku, wunyjurrulu walangkarrangu yajarnayarninyi.
\imt1 Kurrngal yiji muwarr Payipulja. Nyungungungarra mirli-mirlingi jinta murlkurrangu wirrirniyirnijaninyi jukurrangu muwarr. Yijapa karrulunyurru muwarrku makunurranguku yirrilkulunyurru Payipulja.
\imt1 Original postface information
\ip The Nyangumarta title of this book is, “Nyungurrangu Payipulja Muwarrangu. Walangkarranguja Yajarnayarninyi Yakujun.” In English this title means, 'These are Stories From The Bible. From The Beginning They Followed Each Other In This Way'.
\ip Nyangumarta is understood by approximately 1,000 Aborigines living in the eastern half of the Pilbara Region of Western Australia.
\ip This book was originally printed by Mission Publications of Australia (PO Box 21, Lawson NSW 2783) as a Ngaanyatjarra—English edition. The English text at the bottom of the pages was prepared by Amee Glass and Dorothy Hackett of the Ngaanyatjarra Bible Project, Alice Springs, and the equivalent Ngaanyatjarra text was then prepared in collaboration with Ngaanyatjarra speakers, and printed at the top of the pages.
\ip Using that Ngaanyatjarra—English edition as a model, an expanded English text (not included here) was prepared by Brian and Helen Geytenbeek of Wycliffe Bible Translators. It was translated into Nyangumarta under their supervision, and the translation checked by several Nyangumarta speakers, and substituted for the Ngaanyatjarra text in this edition.
\ip The illustrations are by Jack Finch of Mission Publications of Australia.
\ip BIBLE OVERVIEW Inland Nyangumarta 18 Mar 1996.
\c 1
\s1 1
\m (Title Page)
\p Nyungurrangu Payipulja Muwarrangu.
\p Walangkarranguja Yajarnayarninyi Yakujun.
\b
\p These Are Stories From The Bible.
\p From The Beginning They Followed Each Other In This Way.
\b
\p (Nyangumarta language)
\s1 2
\p Ngarrka walangkarranguja waninyi, (Japartupa Partanypa Pirlurr Ngalypakata), palinyjakun.
\b
\p NGARRKA:
\q1 Japartu
\q1 Partany
\q1 Pirlurr Ngalypakata
\s1 3
\p Ngarrkalu parlparrpa jungkapa kujungurru jini. Wiyirr jinijaninyi kujungurrungupa jungkangapa parlparrja. Palaja pirirripa mirtawa pukun jinipulinyi. Marrngu wiyirr, warrarnjarrangu ngurnarrijirrija, milpanyinyi nganyjurru wiyirr nyarrajajirri.
\s1 4
\p Palaja pirirrilupa mirtawalu panypanyapululu Ngarrkanga.
\s1 5
\p Palajalu marrngurrangu wiyirr panypanyakata jarrinyiyi Ngarrkaku ngarramarnti. Kurlu jinakatarrangu jarrinyiyi.
\s1 6
\p Punjaja Ngarrkalu ngakarna wirtu mangkurtu marlkarri jinaku wiyirrku kurlu jinakatarranguku. Wanka jinijaninyi Nawapa palinymili mirtawapa partanykarrangupa ngarrayarrangu, palarrangujakun. Jinta ngapalu warnan kanyajaninyi.
\s1 7
\p Pala mangkurtuja marrngurrangu kurlujartiny ngarrany, panypanyayili yirrkulu Ngarrkanga. Palinyju purlpi wurrarnajanaku, “Jirrja yarrayi warrarnja.” Wurrarnayarningu, “Munu jirrja yankulupiyirni, wantulupiyirni nyungungu kunmu. Yarni malapiyirni wirtujina maya, wirtu warnkukapali, kankakurnu, parlparrkarti.” Palajunjamarra Ngarrkalu yinyajaninyi warinypa wariny muwarr, ngakumpa jarrinyiyarningu. Palajangarra ngunarrijirri yanayi.
\s1 8
\p Walangkarranguja Ngarrkalu wurrarnarningu, “Ngalypa jilamarnajanaku wiyirrku marrngurranguku.” Palajunjalu kuwarri warajanga pirirringi wurrarnalu, yiningi ngapingi, Yayipurayamungu, “Yakalaman nyuntumili warrarn walja. Kaja yiji yankuluman, ngajarrirrangumilikarti warrarnkarti. Yananyaja jurti jilamarnangu ngajulu.” Ngarrkamilija muwarrja yana. Punja waninyi palanga warrarnja warinyja.
\s1 9
\p Yayipurayamu marlkarri jarrinyaja (1,991 BC), palinymili karluji jamujipa janamili partanykarrangu nyirrirnikartija kurrngal jarrinyiyi. Yanayi warrarnkarti warinykarti, Yijipikarti.
\b
\p Yayipurayamu
\q1 Yayijaka
\q2 Jayikapu
\s1 10
\p Punja palanga waninyiyi Yijipingi. Palaja Yijipijalu nyampalirrangulu wily pinapintilu warrkamu jinikinyiyijaninyi marrjalu warnkumajirriku, wirlanangulu.
\s1 11
\p Punjaja Ngarrkalu ngakarnajanaku Muwujuju, wanka jinaku. Muwujujulu kanyajaninyi Yijipija jalakarti. Ngarrkalu wangalju wirtulu larr pini kujungurru, partijirri kaniny pipurru yanayi, punarranga. Yajarniyijaninyi Yijipija jurljarrangulu mananya walarni jinaku. Ngarrkalu kujungurru walarni jinijanaka, wiyirr yamarnajaninyi.
\s1 12
\p Palaja pirranga yanayi. Kujarraja wirlarraja kajarnayi warnku-martaji wirtumartaji. Palanga Ngarrkalu 10 Muwarr Wirturrangu palinymili yinyali Muwujujungu palarranguku marrnguku. Palaja pirranga partunurrangungu 40-ngi miranu jinikinyijaninyi yijalmarta jilipiyili, nganin-nganinku jilipiyi palinymilija muwarrja. Palaja Muwujuju marlkarri jarrinyi. Ngarrkalu manajanaku Jajuwa nyampali.
\s1 13
\p Yayipurayamungu wankanga Ngarrkalu wurrarnala, “Nyuntumilirrangu kurrngal wantulupiyi. Yakalapiyi nyungu warrarn. Punjaja walarni jilamarnajaninyi nyungukarti.” Yartikarra yiji Jajuwalu kanyajaninyi palakartijakun warrarnkarti.
\s1 14
\p Jajuwa marlkarri jarrinyaja yakarnayi Ngarrka, panypanyikinyiyili palinymilingi muwarrja. Palajalu Ngarrkalu kulijarturrangu ngakarnajaninyi wirlana wirntiji pinaku, yarrana pinakarralupiyili, yarrana jilipiyili palinymilija muwarrja.
\s1 15
\p Punjaja (1,050 BC) marrngurrangu panyju karrinyiyalu Ngarrkaku nyampaliku. Wurrarnikinyiya, “Marrnguku karrinyiyirni nyampaliku!” Ngarrkalu manajanaka pirirri kulijartu, yini Juul. Yarti yakarna Ngarrka, warinykurnu yana.
\s1 16
\p Juul marlkarri jarrinyaja (1,010 BC) Ngarrkalu mana Tayipiti, nyampali jinijanaku. Palinyja ngarlungu yiji Ngarrka, pinakarrinyikinyalu, jinikinyi Ngarrkamilija muwarrja. Ngurra jini ngapingi, tawunja, Jirujalamungu.
\s1 17
\p Palaja (970 BC) Jalaman, Tayipitimili partany, nyampali jarrinyijanaku. Palanga tawunja Jirujalamungu yarni marna wirtujina maya Ngarrkaku. Yamarna miji-mijilu karnukapalilu. Pala maya yini marnayi Timpul.
\s1 18
\p Palaja (930 — 603 BC) marlu nyampali jarrinyiyi, manayijaninyi warajapa waraja. Marrngulu yirrkulu panypanyikinyiyili Ngarrkanga. Mungkapa warnku manayijaninyi, marni pinayijaninyi miyu mangunykapalirrangu, palarrangu japirr marnikinyiyijaninyi, “Tuku jilkulunyurrunganinyi.” Nyurra marnikinyiyijaninyi palarrangu, wurrarnikinyiya Ngarrka puru yiji.
\s1 19
\p Palajalu punjaja (603 — 586 BC) Ngarrkalu ngakarnajaninyi jurljarrangu ngajarri marrjalu wirlanaku. Ngartarniyijaninyi tawunarrangu wiyirr, kamparniyi pala wirtu tawun, Jirujalamu, pala Timpul Ngarrkaku pukun kamparniyi, marrngu wiyirr kanyayijaninyi kajakarti warrarnkarti, Papilunkarti.
\s1 20
\p Papilunja waninyaja (586 — 538 BC) kurlkarri marnikinyiyi Ngarrka. Parnpina wirrirniyijaninyi janamili miyu mangunykapalirrangu. Palaja Ngarrkalu walarni jinijaninyi warrarnkarti waljakarti.
\s1 21
\p Palaja (537 — 516 BC) yarrana yarni marnayi pala tawun Jirujalamupa wupartumartajakun timpul.
\s1 22
\p Punjaja (6 BC) Ngarrkalu ngakarna partany walja palinymili, marrngu jarrinyaku. Ngayinyja waninyikinyi, ngurli-ngurli jarrinyi. Palinymililu pipilu, Miyirilu, partany kanya ngapingi, tawunja, Pijiliyamungu, palangangarra ngurli-ngurli miral jarrinyi. Yini marna “Jiyijaji” Ngarrkamilija muwarrja.
\s1 23
\p Palaja (26 — 30 AD) Jiyijaji marrngu jarrinyaja yaninyikinyi miranu jinikinyijaninyi marrngurrangu Ngarrkaku, wurrkujartiny ngalypa jinikinyijaninyipa. Palinyju wurrarnikinyijanaku, “Yijalmarta jilkulunyurrulu Ngarrkanga, yirrkulu jilkulunyurrulu palinymilija muwarrja.”
\s1 24
\p Palaja (30 AD) kurlukata yatilarrangu malyparr karrinyiyili, warlirniyi. Jurljarrangulu parirr kujarranykarti yarntarniyi mungkanga. Jiyijaji marlkarri jarrinyaja warinyju kawu palinymili ngalpa jini jurntingi. Kujarraja warrukartija Ngarrkalu yarrana wanka jini, turlpanya marlkarrija.
\s1 25
\p Palaja (30 AD) 40-ngi karrpungu Jiyijaji marlumal miral jarrinyikinyi-janaku palinymiliku marrngurranguku. Palinyju wurrarnajanaku, “Ngajulu ngakalamarnanyurruku Pirlurr Ngarrkamili Ngalypakata, nyurranga kaninykurtingi wantulunyurruku. Mimalkulunyurralu palinyku.” Palaja Jiyijaji kulpanyalu kanka Ngarrkakarti.
\s1 26
\p Palaja (30 AD) Ngarrkamili Pirlurr Ngalypakata milpanyijanaku kaninykurtiku waninyaku yijalmarta jinakatanga. Palinyju yirrkulu kurlkapirli jilkulinyjaninyi jurtuku, jilkulupiyi Ngarrkamilija muwarrja, miranu jilkulupiyijaninyi wiyirr marrngurrangu Jiyijajiku. Ngani wurralpirtiku Jiyijajilu purlpi miranu jinijaninyi palinymilirrangu, palangarra miranu jinaku jintaku.
\s1 27
\p Palaja (30 AD-ja) muwarr jakul kanganyikinyiyi ngalypakata, “Marlkarri jarrinyajalu Jiyijajilu kartuwarra marnanganyjurrinyi. Palajalu yijalmarta jinakatarrangu kajalapiyili ngarrakuny Ngarrkanga, munu jurtu ngakalkulinyjaninyi.”
\s1 28
\p Punja ngarranyja (30 AD-ja kuwarrikartijakun) Jiyijajingi yijalmarta jinakatarrangulu jakul kanganyi-kinyiyijanaku nyarra muwarr ngunarrijirri, warrarn-jarrangu wiyirrja. Kuwarri nganyjurrulu pukun wurralkuluminyijanaku wiyirrja marrngurrangungu muwarr nyarra ngarrany.
\s1 29
\p Warajanga karrpungu Jiyijaji kulpuliny palinymilija muwarrja. Palangangarra wanka jilkulinyjaninyi yijalmarta jinakatarrangu marlkarrija. Palaja mujungungu kunmu jilkulinyjaninyi nyarrarrangupa wiyirr jinta yijalmarta jinakatarrangu kuwarri wanka waninyayipa, kanka yankulupiyi palinykarti.
\s1 30
\p Palaja kalkulkulinyjaninyi ngarrakuny Ngarrkamilingi warrarnja.
\s1 31
\p Palanga palarrangu Jiyijajingi panypanyakatarrangu Ngarrkalu warnta malkulinyjaninyi. Palaja jurtu ngakalkulinyjaninyi, wantulupiyi kaninykurti wikanga wirtungu ngarramarnti. 
